[30;1m2088 | [0m[35mclock jumps from 1:59 back to 1:00 again, and repeats the 1:MM hour in[0m

[30;1m2090 | [0m[35mUTC hours 5:MM and 6:MM to 1:MM Eastern.  The result is ambiguous[0m

[30;1m230 | [0m[35m----------------------------------------------------------------------------[0m
[30;1m231 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m232 | [0m[35m``python-future`` contains, in addition to the ``future`` compatibility[0m
[30;1m233 | [0m[35mpackage, a ``futurize`` script that is similar to ``python-modernize.py``[0m
[30;1m234 | [0m[35min intent and design. Both are based heavily on ``2to3``.[0m
[30;1m235 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m236 | [0m[35mWhereas ``python-modernize`` converts Py2 code into a common subset of[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1035[0m[34m of [0m[33m1806[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m

[30;1m174 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m175 | [0m[35mThis is not an isolated example; almost every output of ``2to3`` will need[0m
[30;1m176 | [0m[35mmodification to provide backward compatibility with Python 2. As an[0m
[30;1m177 | [0m[35malternative, the ``python-future`` project provides a script called[0m
[30;1m178 | [0m[35m``futurize`` that is based on ``lib2to3`` but will produce code that is[0m
[30;1m179 | [0m[35mcompatible with both platforms (Py2 and Py3).[0m
[30;1m180 | [0m[35m[0m

   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mIf you define a custom ``__str__`` method for any of your classes,[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mfunctions like ``print()`` expect ``__str__`` on Py2 to return a byte[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mstring, whereas on Py3 they expect a (unicode) string.[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mUse the following decorator to map the ``__str__`` to ``__unicode__`` on[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mPy2 and define ``__str__`` to encode it as utf-8::[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1433[0m[34m of [0m[33m1806[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m819 | [0m[35mOne purpose of ``past`` is to ease module-by-module upgrades to[0m
[30;1m820 | [0m[35mcodebases from Python 2. Another is to help with enabling Python 2 libraries to[0m
[30;1m821 | [0m[35msupport Python 3 without breaking the API they currently provide. (For example,[0m
[30;1m822 | [0m[35muser code may expect these libraries to pass them Python 2's 8-bit strings,[0m
[30;1m823 | [0m[35mrather than Python 3's ``bytes`` object.) A third purpose is to help migrate[0m
[30;1m824 | [0m[35mprojects to Python 3 even if one or more dependencies are still on Python 2.[0m
[30;1m825 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m196 | [0m[35mmostly unchanged on both Python 2 and Python 3.[0m

[30;1m155 | [0m[35m    ``u''`` prefixes for unicode literals on Python 3.3+] is at odds with[0m

[30;1m158 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1616[0m[34m of [0m[33m1806[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/future-1.0.0/docs/unicode_literals.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35m~~~~~~~~~[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m51 | [0m[35m1. Adding ``unicode_literals`` to a module amounts to a "global flag day" for[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35m   that module, changing the data types of all strings in the module at once.[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35m   Cautious developers may prefer an incremental approach. (See[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35m   `here <http://lwn.net/Articles/165039/>`_ for an excellent article[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m   describing the superiority of an incremental patch-set in the the case[0m

       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m

[30;1m17 | [0m[35mThis section summarizes the benefits and drawbacks of using[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35m``unicode_literals``. To avoid confusion, we recommend using[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35m``unicode_literals`` everywhere across a code-base or not at all, instead of[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35mturning on for only some modules.[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m144 | [0m[35mIn favour of ``unicode_literals``[0m
[30;1m145 | [0m[35m*********************************[0m
[30;1m146 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m147 | [0m[35mDjango recommends importing ``unicode_literals`` as its top `porting tip <https://docs.djangoproject[0m
[30;1m148 | [0m[35mmigrating Django extension modules to Python 3.  The following `quote[0m
[30;1m149 | [0m[35m<https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/django-developers/2ddIWdicbNY>`_ is[0m
[30;1m150 | [0m[35mfrom Aymeric Augustin on 23 August 2012 regarding why he chose[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1619[0m[34m of [0m[33m1806[0m[31m ]--[0m
